<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Lotus</i> <i>unifoliolatus</i> is dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Agrostis</i> spp., <i>Bidens</i> <i>frondosa</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>hordeaceus</i>, <i>Convolvulus</i> <i>arvensis</i>, <i>Croton</i> <i>setigerus</i>, <i>Epilobium</i> spp., <i>Euthamia</i> <i>occidentalis</i>, <i>Hemizonia</i> <i>congesta</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>brachyantherum</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>arcticus</i>, <i>Lolium</i> <i>perenne</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> spp., <i>Mentha</i> <i>pulegium</i>, <i>Phyla</i> <i>nodiflora</i>, <i>Rumex</i> spp., <i>Trifolium</i> spp., <i>Veronica</i> <i>peregrina</i>, <i>Vulpia</i> <i>myuros</i> and <i>Xanthium</i> <i>strumarium</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 75 cm; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Seasonally to intermittently flooded alluvial flats, stream terraces. Soils are deep loams and alluvial silts. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (2012 national list) recognizes <i>Lotus unifoliolatus</i> var. <i>unifoliolatus</i> as an UPL plant. </div>
</div>

		
